<br>
-PULSE- shock waves pour forth from the enchanters in a palpable wave at the wraithes. The wizards begin to turn in time, hands burning red with wizard fire. They begin to empty their wrath into the colorful demons.<br>
<br>
The wraithes are stunned momentarily, but some resist the shock wave and reach greedily for the source. One enchanter screams as a wraith locks its teeth onto his wrist.<br>
<br>
&quot;They're resisting! Where the hells are my heals??&quot; he shrieks, as his hand is bit from hiswrist.<br>
<br>
&quot;The druid was our healer...&quot; Tremas shouts, spinning, magical flames shooting from his fingertips, sizzling the flesh of the wraithes.<br>
<br>
